The Philippines and the World Bank havesigned a 300 mln dlr loan and 10 mln dlr worth of technicalassistance to help Manila in its economic recovery efforts,bank officials said .    The loan, to be disbursed in three equal tranches, isrepayable over 20 years, including a five-year grace period,with a variable interest rate, currently at 7.92 pct.    The loan was signed by Finance Minister Jaime Ongpin and A.Karasmasoglu, World Bank vice-president for East Asia and thePacific. Ongpin said the first tranche of 100 mln dlrs wasexpected within a month. REUTER&#3;